			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">Citrix is remote-control on a terminal server.  All that the client PC gets is the video in and the keyboard/mouse out.  Any work/records are on the server at work.

On top of that, each terminal services session is generally unique, and there is no way for you to log in to (husband's) session to see what he'd been doing, because it'll generally be new, with no history.

Plus, for you to attempt to do so without express permission from his employer would be illegal.</span>
		</div>
           
