			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">I'm not trained in any of this, although i find your blogs fascinating (my partner is a unix admin who's job it is to keep on top of networks at work, so i am slowly learning about the murky world of IT security!).. however from a non-techie point of view.. one obvious method must be.. if the information can't leave the box.. then.. if the mountain cannot come to mohammed.. mohammed must go to the mountain. You could install the spyware you mentioned and then arrange with Donna to view it ON the husband's box. 



Or, if Donna - from a legal point of view - owns the box and the information within, (the basis on which you viewed it in the first place), and gave you permission to "image" it and view it on your third party network; she could, in theory, administrate the spy software herself and email/burn a CD and send it to you with the permission THEN to view it on your third party network. However, i have no knowledge of this spyware (as must be painfully apparent - stop wincing, guys!) so i don't know if this would be workable or practical.



just a few thoughts from a non-techie type person who finds this all absolutely FASCINATING!



kethry

