Install a keylogger on the box and configure it to encrypt and email outputs to your mailbox. The outputs will only show what Donna's husband keys-in and not the responses, so no third party privacy violations there! In case you find something objectionable in the key-ins from your client's viewpoint then visit the husband's company, tell the guys there about situation you have on hand and that the company might actually benifit from your investigations. Should not be difficult from there, I guess ?  Was it?



