            </div>
			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">I'm looking at this from a UK perspective and guess that Computer Misuse legislation is similar in both countries.



Let's go back to the beginning.  Why was Chief asked to conduct this investigation?  Because Donna suspected that her husband was cheating on her.  Now, why is everyone beginning to suspect that Donna's husband is up to all sorts of crime?  That's just pure speculation and will only divert you from the main issue Chief is here to resolve.  Is Donna's husband cheating or not?  There's just no proof so far!



As I'm not familar with your laws I cannot comment on the technical route you can or are able to take.  It takes "2 to tango" so why not switch to physical surveillance methods.  If Donna's husband is having an affair then he must meet that other party sometime.



Bob</span>
		</div>
           
